bilbycast-edge (full variant)
=============================

This binary is a combined work distributed under the terms of the
GNU Affero General Public License, version 3 or later
(AGPL-3.0-or-later). See LICENSE (and COPYING.GPL for the GPL-3.0
text that covers libx264 / libx265 via their GPL-2.0-or-later
upgrade clause).

The bilbycast source code is offered under two licences, at your
choice:

 1. AGPL-3.0-or-later (LICENSE) — the default for open-source users.
 2. A commercial licence from Softside Tech Pty Ltd — for OEMs,
    hardware integrators, SaaS providers, and other commercial
    users who need to embed or operate bilbycast without AGPL's
    copyleft. Contact commercial@softsidetech.com for terms. See
    LICENSE.commercial.

The combination with libx264 and libx265 (both GPL-2.0-or-later) is
permitted because AGPL-3.0 is explicitly GPL-3.0-compatible
(AGPL § 13) and libx264 / libx265 may be redistributed under
GPL-3.0 via their "or later" clause. The full GPL-3.0 text is at
COPYING.GPL for reference.

Important: a Softside commercial licence covers the bilbycast source
code only. It does not — and cannot — relicense libx264 or libx265,
which are owned by VideoLAN and MulticoreWare respectively. If you
distribute this `-full` binary under a commercial licence, the
libx264 and libx265 portions of the combined work remain subject to
GPL-2.0-or-later, and their copyleft obligations (source offer,
preservation of licence notices, no additional restrictions) continue
to apply. Commercial customers who need to avoid GPL entirely should
use the default variant (no software video encoders) or build with
`video-encoder-nvenc` only — NVENC's API layer is LGPL-compatible
and patent coverage is provided by NVIDIA at the hardware/driver
layer. See LICENSE.commercial for the full scope statement.

