Source code availability
------------------------

The complete corresponding source code for this binary is available
across the bilbycast repositories on GitHub at the matching tag:

    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-edge/tree/v{VER}
    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-srt/tree/v{VER}
    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-libsrt-rs/tree/v{VER}
    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-rist/tree/v{VER}
    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-fdk-aac-rs/tree/v{VER}
    https://github.com/<org>/bilbycast-ffmpeg-video-rs/tree/v{VER}

Per AGPL-3.0 § 6, a written offer valid for three years to provide
the source on physical media is available on request at
reza@softsidetech.com.

If you modify bilbycast and operate it as a network service,
AGPL § 13 requires you to make the complete corresponding source
code of your modified version available to your users. The
commercial licence from Softside Tech removes that obligation.

Patent notice
-------------

H.264 / AVC and H.265 / HEVC are patent-encumbered codecs.
Separate patent licences may be required from MPEG-LA, Access
Advance, Velos Media, and other rights holders for commercial
deployments that encode or decode these codecs. The bilbycast
project and its maintainers make no representation that any such
patent licences are granted with this binary. Operators are
responsible for obtaining patent licences appropriate to their
jurisdiction and use case.

NVENC on NVIDIA hardware carries separate patent coverage paid by
NVIDIA at the hardware layer; this is often the lowest-friction
commercial path for production H.264 / H.265 encode.

This notice is not legal advice. Consult a qualified IP attorney
for your specific deployment.
